  <Name>k__BackingField: 2 Timothy
  fancyName: 
  nickname: 2ti
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: Greetings from Paul
      content: '  This letter is from Paul, chosen by the will of God to be an apostle
        of Christ Jesus. I have been sent out to tell others about the life he has
        promised through faith in Christ Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Encouragement to Be Faithful
      content: 'I am writing to Timothy, my dear son.May God the Father and Christ
        Jesus our Lord give you grace, mercy, and peace.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Timothy, I thank God for you\u2014the God I serve with a clear conscience,
        just as my ancestors did. Night and day I constantly remember you in my prayers. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I long to see you again, for I remember your tears as we parted.
        And I will be filled with joy when we are together again.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I remember your genuine faith, for you share the faith that first
        filled your grandmother Lois and your mother, Eunice. And I know that same
        faith continues strong in you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is why I remind you to fan into flames the spiritual gift God
        gave you when I laid my hands on you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For God has not given us a spirit of fear and timidity, but of power,
        love, and self-discipline.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So never be ashamed to tell others about our Lord. And don\u2019t
        be ashamed of me, either, even though I\u2019m in prison for him. With the
        strength God gives you, be ready to suffer with me for the sake of the Good
        News. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For God saved us and called us to live a holy life. He did this,
        not because we deserved it, but because that was his plan from before the
        beginning of time\u2014to show us his grace through Christ Jesus. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And now he has made all of this plain to us by the appearing of Christ
        Jesus, our Savior. He broke the power of death and illuminated the way to
        life and immortality through the Good News. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And God chose me to be a preacher, an apostle, and a teacher of this
        Good News.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That is why I am suffering here in prison. But I am not ashamed of
        it, for I know the one in whom I trust, and I am sure that he is able to
        guard what I have entrusted to him[[COMMENT(0)]] until the day of his return.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:12 '
        content: Or <b>what has been entrusted to me.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Hold on to the pattern of wholesome teaching you learned from me\u2014a
        pattern shaped by the faith and love that you have in Christ Jesus. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Through the power of the Holy Spirit who lives within us, carefully
        guard the precious truth that has been entrusted to you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As you know, everyone from the province of Asia has deserted me\u2014even
        Phygelus and Hermogenes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May the Lord show special kindness to Onesiphorus and all his family
        because he often visited and encouraged me. He was never ashamed of me because
        I was in chains. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When he came to Rome, he searched everywhere until he found me. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Good Soldier of Christ Jesus
      content: '  Timothy, my dear son, be strong through the grace that God gives
        you in Christ Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have heard me teach things that have been confirmed by many reliable
        witnesses. Now teach these truths to other trustworthy people who will be
        able to pass them on to others.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Endure suffering along with me, as a good soldier of Christ Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Soldiers don\u2019t get tied up in the affairs of civilian life,
        for then they cannot please the officer who enlisted them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And athletes cannot win the prize unless they follow the rules. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And hardworking farmers should be the first to enjoy the fruit of
        their labor. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Think about what I am saying. The Lord will help you understand all
        these things.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Always remember that Jesus Christ, a descendant of King David, was
        raised from the dead. This is the Good News I preach. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And because I preach this Good News, I am suffering and have been
        chained like a criminal. But the word of God cannot be chained. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I am willing to endure anything if it will bring salvation and
        eternal glory in Christ Jesus to those God has chosen.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is a trustworthy saying:If we die with him,we will also live
        with him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If we endure hardship,we will reign with him.If we deny him,he will
        deny us.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If we are unfaithful,he remains faithful,for he cannot deny who he
        is.  '
      comments: []
    - title: An Approved Worker
      content: "Remind everyone about these things, and command them in God\u2019s
        presence to stop fighting over words. Such arguments are useless, and they
        can ruin those who hear them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Work hard so you can present yourself to God and receive his approval.
        Be a good worker, one who does not need to be ashamed and who correctly explains
        the word of truth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Avoid worthless, foolish talk that only leads to more godless behavior. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This kind of talk spreads like cancer,[[COMMENT(0)]] as in the case
        of Hymenaeus and Philetus. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:17 '
        content: Greek <b>gangrene.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'They have left the path of truth, claiming that the resurrection
        of the dead has already occurred; in this way, they have turned some people
        away from the faith.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But God\u2019s truth stands firm like a foundation stone with this
        inscription: \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> knows those who are his,\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and \u201CAll who belong to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> must turn away
        from evil.\u201D[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:19a '
        content: Num 16:5.
      - number: '2:19b '
        content: See Isa 52:11.
    - title: 
      content: 'In a wealthy home some utensils are made of gold and silver, and
        some are made of wood and clay. The expensive utensils are used for special
        occasions, and the cheap ones are for everyday use. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you keep yourself pure, you will be a special utensil for honorable
        use. Your life will be clean, and you will be ready for the Master to use
        you for every good work.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Run from anything that stimulates youthful lusts. Instead, pursue
        righteous living, faithfulness, love, and peace. Enjoy the companionship
        of those who call on the Lord with pure hearts.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Again I say, don\u2019t get involved in foolish, ignorant arguments
        that only start fights. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A servant of the Lord must not quarrel but must be kind to everyone,
        be able to teach, and be patient with difficult people. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Gently instruct those who oppose the truth. Perhaps God will change
        those people\u2019s hearts, and they will learn the truth. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Dangers of the Last Days
      content: '  You should know this, Timothy, that in the last days there will
        be very difficult times. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For people will love only themselves and their money. They will be
        boastful and proud, scoffing at God, disobedient to their parents, and ungrateful.
        They will consider nothing sacred. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will be unloving and unforgiving; they will slander others and
        have no self-control. They will be cruel and hate what is good. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will betray their friends, be reckless, be puffed up with pride,
        and love pleasure rather than God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will act religious, but they will reject the power that could
        make them godly. Stay away from people like that!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are the kind who work their way into people\u2019s homes and
        win the confidence of[[COMMENT(0)]] vulnerable women who are burdened with
        the guilt of sin and controlled by various desires. "
      comments:
      - number: '3:6 '
        content: Greek <b>and take captive.</b>
    - title: 
      content: '(Such women are forever following new teachings, but they are never
        able to understand the truth.) '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These teachers oppose the truth just as Jannes and Jambres opposed
        Moses. They have depraved minds and a counterfeit faith. '
      comments: []
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Charge to Timothy"
      content: "But they won\u2019t get away with this for long. Someday everyone
        will recognize what fools they are, just as with Jannes and Jambres.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you, Timothy, certainly know what I teach, and how I live, and
        what my purpose in life is. You know my faith, my patience, my love, and
        my endurance. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You know how much persecution and suffering I have endured. You know
        all about how I was persecuted in Antioch, Iconium, and Lystra\u2014but the
        Lord rescued me from all of it. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, and everyone who wants to live a godly life in Christ Jesus
        will suffer persecution. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But evil people and impostors will flourish. They will deceive others
        and will themselves be deceived.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you must remain faithful to the things you have been taught.
        You know they are true, for you know you can trust those who taught you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have been taught the holy Scriptures from childhood, and they
        have given you the wisdom to receive the salvation that comes by trusting
        in Christ Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All Scripture is inspired by God and is useful to teach us what is
        true and to make us realize what is wrong in our lives. It corrects us when
        we are wrong and teaches us to do what is right. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  I solemnly urge you in the presence of God and Christ Jesus, who
        will someday judge the living and the dead when he comes to set up his Kingdom: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Preach the word of God. Be prepared, whether the time is favorable
        or not. Patiently correct, rebuke, and encourage your people with good teaching.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For a time is coming when people will no longer listen to sound and
        wholesome teaching. They will follow their own desires and will look for
        teachers who will tell them whatever their itching ears want to hear. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will reject the truth and chase after myths.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But you should keep a clear mind in every situation. Don\u2019t be
        afraid of suffering for the Lord. Work at telling others the Good News, and
        fully carry out the ministry God has given you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As for me, my life has already been poured out as an offering to
        God. The time of my death is near. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have fought the good fight, I have finished the race, and I have
        remained faithful. '
      comments: []
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Final Words"
      content: "And now the prize awaits me\u2014the crown of righteousness, which
        the Lord, the righteous Judge, will give me on the day of his return. And
        the prize is not just for me but for all who eagerly look forward to his
        appearing.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Timothy, please come as soon as you can. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Demas has deserted me because he loves the things of this life and
        has gone to Thessalonica. Crescens has gone to Galatia, and Titus has gone
        to Dalmatia. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Only Luke is with me. Bring Mark with you when you come, for he will
        be helpful to me in my ministry. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I sent Tychicus to Ephesus. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you come, be sure to bring the coat I left with Carpus at Troas.
        Also bring my books, and especially my papers.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:13 '
        content: Greek <b>especially the parchments.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Alexander the coppersmith did me much harm, but the Lord will judge
        him for what he has done. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Be careful of him, for he fought against everything we said.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The first time I was brought before the judge, no one came with me.
        Everyone abandoned me. May it not be counted against them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the Lord stood with me and gave me strength so that I might preach
        the Good News in its entirety for all the Gentiles to hear. And he rescued
        me from certain death.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:17 '
        content: Greek <b>from the mouth of a lion.</b>
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Final Greetings"
      content: 'Yes, and the Lord will deliver me from every evil attack and will
        bring me safely into his heavenly Kingdom. All glory to God forever and ever!
        Amen.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give my greetings to Priscilla and Aquila and those living in the
        household of Onesiphorus. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Erastus stayed at Corinth, and I left Trophimus sick at Miletus.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do your best to get here before winter. Eubulus sends you greetings,
        and so do Pudens, Linus, Claudia, and all the brothers and sisters.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:21 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers.</b>
